 Of Sourcing) and Joseph Ortega (PAA Head) are active but neither controls budget; without CFO sponsorship they cannot close.", "Forecast is Best Case but lacks an engaged EB, a confirmed 2026 budget and locked commercials, so the category is indefensible."], "headline": "Live but slow: procurement contacts (Joseph Ortega, Rogeliza) are engaged and Zycus is being presented internally as SAP Ariba renewals near, but the formal RFP has slipped repeatedly for two years, the economic buyer (CFO) has not been engaged since Jul 2024, and the deal value was cut from 650K to 350K on 6 Jun 2026. Close by 31 Dec 2026 is not credible on current pace.", "forecast_defensible": false, "recommended_forecast": "Pipeline"}, "competitive_position": {"summary": "SAP Ariba (incumbent) is the single strongest current threat: contract extended 3 months and renewals approaching per 6 Jun 2026, so the dominant risk is a do-nothing renewal, not a rival platform. Coupa ran a workshop before Zycus (31 Jul 2024) but shows no recent buyer lean and ranks below the incumbent. iValua is named only in the field with no corroborating evidence and is dormant. Zycus was indicated to be leading in 2024 (Rogeliza, 16 Sep 2024) with the AI/Merlin story and the GCash reference as the wedge.", "competitors": [{"date": "2026-06-06", "name": "SAP Ariba", "quote": "Ariba contract extended 3 months (22 Aug 2024); Ariba renewals are approaching and Joseph is presenting Zycus internally as the alternative (6 Jun 2026).", "source": "SF Next_Step__c 22 Aug 2024 + 6 Jun 2026, SF Competitors__c", "status": "incumbent", "sentiment": "negative", "how_we_win": "Make the switching-cost and Ariba-renewal-avoidance case concrete and land agentic AI/Merlin as the capability the incumbent cannot match before renewal locks.", "threat_level": "high"}, {"date": "2024-07-31", "name": "Coupa", "quote": "Jerry wants a workshop, Coupa has done already (31 Jul 2024).", "source": "SF Next_Step__c 31 Jul 2024, SF Competitors__c", "st