dget authority; needs to convert access into CFO sponsorship.", "role": "Champion", "email": "rvrana@globe.com.ph", "title": "Head Of Sourcing", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "positive", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2026-06-06"}, {"name": "Joseph Ortega", "risk": "Developing champion presenting Zycus internally; influence over the award not yet proven.", "role": "Champion", "email": "joseph.ortega@globe.com.ph", "title": "PaL - Process, Automation and Analytics (PAA) Head", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "positive", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2026-06-02"}, {"name": "Walter Ricarte", "risk": "Finance decision maker not engaged since Jul 2024; secondary to the CFO on budget.", "role": "Decision Maker", "email": "wcricarte@globe.com.ph", "title": "VP - Finance and Business Advisory", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "neutral", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2024-07-31"}, {"name": "Jackie Fiesta", "risk": "Owns integration sign-off (Ariba-linked subsystems, Maximo); not recently engaged and could surface technical risk.", "role": "Influencer", "email": "jcfiesta@globe.com.ph", "title": "IT Director for Supply Chain, Source-to-Pay, Order-to-Cash and Contract Lifecycle Management", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "neutral", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2024-10-25"}, {"name": "DOROTHEO HONESTO\tOLIVA", "role": "Influencer", "email": "dpoliva@globe.com.ph", "title": "Manager-Vendor Management", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "_role_inferred": true}, {"name": "Zoraida Arellano", "role": "Influencer", "email": "zparellano@globe.com.ph", "title": "Contract Manager", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "_role_inferred": true}]}, "meddpicc": {"metrics": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["SF Next_Step__c 6 Jun 2026", "SF Next_Step__c 31 Jul 2024", "SF Products__c"], "narrative": "The business problem is articulated qualitatively but never quantified. Globe is looking to displace or replace SAP Ariba across S2P (iContract, iSource, iSupplier, eProcurement, eInvoicing, iRequest per Products__c), driven by approaching Ariba renewals (Joseph Ortega, per 6 Jun 2026 Next Step) and a CEO-level appetite for AI-driven transformation (31 Jul 2024 Next Step: Ernest eager for AI but thinks his team are not mature enough, needs our help). No ROI, savings, cycle-time or headcount number has been stated in any field or activity. Quantifying switching value versus the Ariba renewal cost is the move that converts this to confirmed."}, "champion": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["OpportunityContactRole Rogeliza Rana (Head Of Sourcing)", "OpportunityContactRole Joseph Ortega (PAA Head)", "SF Next_Step__c 16 Sep 2024", "SF activities 13 Apr / 29 May / 2 Jun 2026"], "narrative": "Rogeliza Rana (Head Of Sourcing) is the confirmed champion: she confidentially indicated Zycus was leading the evaluation at the Summit (16 Sep 2024), provided a warm intro to the new CFO (13 Feb), and is named in the 6 Jun 2026 F2F plan to consolidate Zycus mindshare. Joseph Ortega (PAA Head) has developed into an active second champion, sending inbound inquiries (13 Apr, 29 May, 2 Jun 2026 on the Supply Chain Risk module) and offering to present Zycus internally to management as Ariba renewals near. What is developed: two engaged procurement advocates driving internal presentations; what is still missing: neither controls budget, and their access to the CFO has not been exercised recently, so champion strength has not yet been converted into executive sponsorship."}, "competition": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["SF Competitors__c (Coupa;iValua;SAP Ariba)", "SF Next_Step__c 22 Aug 2024", "SF Next_Step__c 31 Jul 2024", "SF Next_Step__c 6 Jun 2026"], "narrative": "SAP Ariba is the incumbent and the single strongest current threat: the contract was extended 3 months (22 Aug 2024) and renewals are approaching (6 Jun 2026), so the real risk is a low-friction do-nothing renewal rather than a switch to a new platform. Coupa is a named alternative that ran an evaluation workshop before Zycus (31 Jul 2024) but shows no recent buyer lean. iValua appears only in the Competitors__c field with no call or Next Step corroboration. Zycus's wedge is the AI/Merlin narrative (a Chief AI Officer audience and formal AI clarifications), the GCash reference win, and champion advocacy indicating Zycus was leading in 2024; the way to win is to make the switching-cost case against the Ariba renewal and land the agentic-AI differentiation the incumbent cannot match."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["SF Next_Step__c 6 Jun 2026", "SF Next_Step__c 31 Jul 2024", "SF Next_Step__c 19 Jun 2024"], "narrative": "The confirmed pain is the approaching SAP Ariba renewal decision and a mandate to modernise procurement with AI, articulated qualitatively. Joseph Ortega is presenting Zycus internally because Ariba renewals are approaching (6 Jun 2026), and the CEO wants AI-driven transformation but views his team as not yet mature enough (31 Jul 2024). Inferred pain includes integration complexity across Ariba-linked subsystems (IT assessment 25 Oct 2024, Maximo rationalisation) and capex pressure across the group (19 Jun 2024). The pain owner is procurement leadership (Jerry Cabiles VP, Rogeliza Rana), with the AI mandate owned at board level via Anton Reynaldo Bonifacio. No dollar or efficiency figure has been attached to the pain."}, "paper_process": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["SF Next_Step__c 10 Jun 2024", "SF Next_Step__c 22 Aug 2024", "OpportunityContactRole Ria Caganda-Vistan, Luwell Manlapig"], "narrative": "Contracting mechanics are largely unknown for Globe itself. The clearest signal is the intent to combine GCash and Globe into a single contract (10 Jun 2024) and legal engagement on the GCash side (CLM demo for legal 14 Jun 2024), with named legal contacts on the account (Ria Caganda-Vistan, AVP Head of Business Enabling & M&A Legal Serv